Leo pressed himself against the vibrating glass of the drink cooler, eyes wide, the orange puff dust clinging to his shirt. Yet, amidst the deafening chaos, he saw Al, miraculously untouched behind the counter, simply sigh. It was a sound of profound annoyance rather than terror. He put down the energy bar he was holding with deliberate slowness.\
