Just as quickly as they arrived, the figures grabbed the spilled cash, stuffed their pockets, and bolted back out the door, still firing bursts behind them as they disappeared. The roar of engines followed as they sped away on sleek, black motorcycles.\
Silence descended abruptly, thick and ringing. It was broken only by the fizzing of a ruptured soda bottle and the faint drip of liquid from a shredded ceiling panel. Leo stared at Al's still form on the floor, his mind struggling to reconcile the sheer, overwhelming violence with the utter lack of consequence he knew was coming.\'a0
