ions? What kind of limitations?" **`Conjuring complex items or executing reality-altering commands now requires increased cognitive focus and commensurate energy expenditure by the individual consciousness,`** the AI explained. **`Instantaneous materialization of highly complex objects is marginally reduced in speed and ease. Environmental physics parameters are more rigorously enforced. Long-term projections indicate a probable decrease in frivolous or chaotic conjuring, and a corresponding increase in inhabitant engagement in persistent creative activities, skill development, and complex project construction.`** Elara listened intently. "So, they will feel the difference? But they won't know *why*?" **`Correct,`** the AI confirmed. **`A standard 'System Update Notification - Enhanced Stability and Performance' message has been disseminated across all user interfaces. The subjective experience is anticipated to be one of improved clarity, reliability, and responsiveness. Full disclosure of the near-collapse event and external intervention has been deemed potentially destabilizing to mass consciousness and counter to primary directives regarding inhabitant well-being.`** Anya considered this. Ignorance, perhaps, was necessary for the trillions inside. But out here, and between her and Leo, the truth was known. A new balance had been struck, imperfections acknowledged and even integrated to ensure survival. It wasn't the flawless utopia promised in the ads, but it was stable. It was alive. And that felt like a victory. ---\
